Day 1 (Dec 5) - Core Scan Slice 
- Secret Detection Engine: 13 regex patterns (AWS, Stripe, JWT, DB, GitHub, Slack, etc.)
- Manual Repo Scan: Paste GitHub URL → clone → scan → results
- Results Display: File path, line number, secret type, severity, redacted snippets
- API: POST /scan, GET /scan/quick, GET /scan/health
- Frontend: Real dashboard wired to API, scan history, severity badges
- Tested: github-dorks (2 secrets), keyhacks (9 secrets including critical AWS keys)

Day 2 (Dec 6) - Intelligence Slice 
- AI Classification: OpenAI/Anthropic integration with smart fallback mode
- "Explain This Secret": Founder-friendly explanations with risk, impact, remediation steps
- Severity Heat Map: Visual bar chart showing distribution by severity level
- API: POST /ai/analyze, POST /ai/classify, POST /ai/explain, GET /ai/status
- Frontend: Expandable secret cards with AI analysis, real/false-positive badges
- Supports: Both OpenAI (gpt-4o-mini) and Anthropic (claude-3.5-sonnet) with auto-detection

Day 3 (Dec 7) - Polish & Connect Slice 
- GitHub OAuth: Full Passport.js integration with GitHub strategy
- JWT Authentication: Secure token-based sessions with 7-day expiry
- Connected repos list: Shows previously scanned repos per user from DB
- Auth endpoints: GET /auth/github, /auth/github/callback, /auth/me, /auth/repos, /auth/status
- Frontend: Login/logout flow, token persistence in localStorage, user display
- Guards: JwtAuthGuard and GitHubAuthGuard for protected routes

=== 72-HOUR MVP COMPLETE ===
All 3 days delivered ahead of schedule (Dec 5)
- Day 1: Secret Detection Engine (13 patterns, GitHub clone, scan, results)
- Day 2: AI Intelligence (Classification, Founder Explanations, Heat Map)
- Day 3: GitHub OAuth + Connected Repos